The revered descendant of Ahlul Bayt faced prolonged confinement within a Baghdad prison, where Harun al-Rashid ordered lethal intoxication leading to his passing on 25th Rajab. This tragedy highlights resistance against oppression, spiritual endurance, and unwavering devotion, making the remembrance of seventh Shia Imam shahadat a powerful symbol of patience, faith, and divine leadership for believers worldwide. On his shahadat many laments are recited like syedi mola raza da baba, aj baghdad main koi qaidi.
